data.description: Under contract-accepting backup offers. One or more photo(s) has been virtually staged. ***This property is eligible for St. Pete’s Down Payment Assistance program with up to $60k in assistance to first-time buyers, and can be stacked with a separate $7500 Grant & $500 Appraisal credit! See info in MLS docs *** Welcome to this charming 3-bedroom, 1-bath home built in 2000, offering both comfort and convenience. Inside, you'll find a thoughtfully designed layout with the added bonus of inside laundry. The Seller is offering up to a $5,000 CREDIT to assist in closing costs for buyers.   Situated on a corner lot, the property boasts a fully fenced yard, providing both privacy and security. Alley access adds an extra layer of accessibility. Just minutes away from downtown St. Pete, and with easy access to 275, commuting to and from Bradenton or Tampa is a breeze. The welcoming LARGE covered front porch, provides the perfect spot to engage with the vibrant community, and to share moments with friends and family.  Recent updates & improvements include. BRAND NEW ROOF, HVAC Recently Installed, Newer flooring throughout adds a touch of modern elegance, full roof replacement, completed less than 30 days ago, ensures peace of mind. The HVAC system has been professionally installed, offering energy efficiency and comfort.  This home is not only affordable, but it also offers ample space. The fully fenced backyard is a versatile space, perfect for entertaining or storing trailers, boats, RVs including shore connection electrical hook up for an RV. A LARGE freestanding shed on concrete pad offers secure storage in the FULL FENCED backyard. Large Gate with side access provides both convenience and security.  Don't miss out on this opportunity to own a spacious, well-maintained home in a prime location. Schedule your showing today!
